style=\"background:#fbb\"\n| [[Anthony Sherman]] || FB || Yes\n|- style=\"background:#fbb\"\n| [[De'Anthony Thomas]] || WR || Yes\n|- style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs}}\"\n| [[Spencer Ware]] || RB || No\n|- style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs}}\"\n| [[Charcandrick West]] || RB || No\n|-\n| [[Frank Zombo]] || OLB || No\n|}\n{|class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs}};width:20px; em;\"| Signed with new team\n!style=\"background:#fbb\"| Re-signed\n|}\n{{small|*As of August 20}}\n\n===Restricted free agents===\nBelow are players with expiring contracts that have three or fewer accrued seasons with the Chiefs that can receive a qualifying offer from any NFL team, the Chiefs can chose to either match the offer or receive a draft pick as compensation depending on the tender placed by the Chiefs which can be 1st round, 2nd, or original round (the pick that was used to draft the player). If no offer sheet is given, the player will receive a one year contract with the Chiefs for a salary based on the tender placed on the player, $2.879 million for a first, $2.023 million for a second, or $1.323 million for an original round tender. If a tender is not placed, the player becomes an unrestricted free agent.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs|year=2019|border=2}}\"| RFAs\n|-\n! Player || Position || Tender || Qualifying offer || Matched?*\n|-\n| [[Jordan Lucas]] || FS || Original round (6th) || None<br>Signed tender || N/A\n|-\n| [[Terrance Smith (linebacker)|Terrance Smith]] || ILB || Not placed || None || N/A\n|}\n\n{{small|*As of April 15}}\n\n===Exclusive-rights free agents===\nBelow are players with two or fewer seasons of tenure with expiring contracts. If the Chiefs makes a qualifying offer (a one-year contract usually at league-minimum salary) the player has no negotiating rights with other teams, and must either sign the tender with the Chiefs or sit out the 2019 season. If a qualifying offer is not made, the player is an unrestricted free agent.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs|year=2019|border=2}}\"| ERFAs\n|-\n! Player || Position || Qualifying offer?* || Signed?\u2020\n|-\n| [[Harrison Butker]] || K || Yes || Yes\n|-\n| [[Alex Ellis (American football)|Alex Ellis]] || TE || No || N/A\n|-\n| [[Justin Hamilton (defensive lineman)|Justin Hamilton]] || NT || Yes || Yes\n|-\n| [[Marcus Kemp]] || WR || Yes || Yes\n|}\n\n{{small|*As of March 13<br>\u2020As of April 15}}\n\n===Trades===\nBelow are any trades that included at least one player. Trades that featured only draft picks being traded for both teams, are listed in NFL Draft section.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs|year=2019|border=2}}\"| Trades\n|-\n! Player(s)/Pick(s)<br>Received || Team || Compensation\n|-\n| 2nd round pick<br>[[2020 NFL Draft]] || [[San Francisco 49ers]] || LB [[Dee Ford]]\n|-\n| DE [[Emmanuel Ogbah]] || [[Cleveland Browns]] || S [[Eric Murray (American football)|Eric Murray]]\n|-\n| DE [[Frank Clark (American football)|Frank Clark]]<br>3rd round pick<br>2019 Draft || [[Seattle Seahawks]] || 1st & 3rd round pick<br>2019 NFL Draft<br>2nd round pick<br>2020 NFL Draft\n|-\n| LB [[Darron Lee]] || [[New York Jets]] || 6th round pick<br>2020 NFL Draft\n|}\n\n===Draft===\n{{main|2019 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs|year=2019|border=2}}\"| 2019 Kansas City Chiefs Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| 2 || 56\n| [[Mecole Hardman]] || [[Wide Receiver]] || [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]]\n|-\n! 63\n| [[Juan Thornhill]] || [[Safety (gridiron football position)|Safety]] || [[Virginia Cavaliers football|Virginia]]\n|-\n! 3 || 84\n| [[Khalen Saunders]] || [[Defensive tackle]] || [[Western Illinois Leathernecks football|Western Illinois]]\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| 6 || 201\n| [[Rashad Fenton]] || [[Cornerback]] || [[South Carolina Gamecocks football|South Carolina]]\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs}}\"| 214*\n| [[Darwin Thompson]] || [[Running back]] || [[Utah State Aggies football|Utah State]]\n|-\n! 7 || 216\n| [[Nick Allegretti]] || [[Guard (American and Canadian football)|Guard]] || [[Illinois Fighting Illini football|Illinois]]\n|}\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Kansas City Chiefs}}; text-align:center; width:20px; em;\"| *\n| [[National Football League draft#Compensatory picks|Compensatory selection]]\n|}\n'''Draft pick trades''' \n*The Chiefs received a sixth round pick in the [[2018 NFL Draft]] and a second round pick in the 2019 NFL Draft in exchange for cornerback [[Marcus Peters]] and a fourth round pick in the 2018 NFL Draft.\n*The Chiefs traded a fourth round pick in the 2019 NFL Draft in exchange for linebacker [[Reggie Ragland]].\n*The Chiefs traded wide receiver [[Rod Streater]] and a seventh round pick in the 2019 NFL Draft to the [[San Francisco 49ers]] in exchange for a seventh round pick in the 2019 NFL Draft.\n*The Chiefs traded their first round (29th overall) in the 2019 NFL Draft, their third round (92nd overall) selection in the 2019 Draft, and a 2nd round selection in the 2020 draft to the [[Seattle Seahawks]] in exchange for defensive end [[Frank Clark (American football)|Frank Clark]] and the Seahawks 3rd round selection (84th overall) in the 2019 NFL Draft.\n*The Chiefs traded a second round selection (61st overall) and their 5th round selection (167th overall) to Los Angeles Rams in exchange for the Rams 2nd round selection (56th overall)\n\n===Staff===\n{{NFL final staff\n|Year=2019\n|TeamName=Kansas City Chiefs\n|Front Office=\n*Chairman/CEO \u2013 [[Clark Hunt]]\n*President \u2013 [[Mark Donovan (American football)|Mark Donovan]]\n*General mana